•    All MNP & new sales will get Jazz Champion’s by default
•    Other package subscribers can migrate to Jazz Champions by dialing *337#
•    Call set up fee Rs. 0.15 is applicable
•    Actual internet speed will depend on multiple factors like sim, device, web pages accessed, time of day, number of simultaneous users, distance from 2G/3G/4G site etc
•    If you are not subscribed to any data bundle, base rate will be charged i.e. Rs.5/MB. Charging Pulse will be 512 KB

Customer can avail this bundle from our self-service channels i.e., 3111 Self-Service IVR.

Social media includes Twitter, Facebook & whatsapp

On-Net minutes are useable for calls to Warid Network as well
Free minutes and FnF Min will not available during IR
Packages are recursive in charging (monthly) and pro-ratable
No CPP charges will be applied on these packages
GPRS rates would be the Rs.18/MB with 64KB minimum charging unit
Package is available to consumer catalogue only & not business

An FnF number added or updated cannot be deleted again on the same day. Delete action can only work from the next day
If an FnF number ports out, the FnF discount will no longer apply to calls made to it

Package Conversion Charges: Rs. 15 + tax, Rs.17.95 (inc tax)

Note: 1st time package plan conversion is free  

UPDATE: Please note that effective 14th March 2024 11:59PM below mentioned discounted voice payg rates will NOT be available for Jazz One service class. Normal call rates mentioned above (3.50/60 sec) will be charged to the customer. Customer having main account balance less than PKR 3.65 (Call base rate + Call setup charges) will not be able to intiate the call.

Voice PayG Pilot (Starting from 12th Sep- Expired: 14th March 2024 11:59PM)

We are conducting a pilot on Jazz One service class for discounted voice payg rates at balance less than Rs.3.65. Customers having balance less than Rs.3.65 will be able to generate a new payg call and be charged based below banding for available balance.

Important Points:

  • We are currently charging customers voice payg rate @ Rs.3.5 per min (Rs. 3.65 including call setup charge)
  • These rates will only apply on new calls.
  • In case of low balance, on-going call will disconnect, and customer will then be able to dial a new call at discounted rate.
  • These rates will be applicable on both on-net & off-net Min however will not be applicable below Rs. 1.15 balance
  • Rest of the existing mechanics will remain same

column36:
On-Net minutes are useable for calls to Warid Network as well
J-600 Price plan customers now have 2,000 SMS as package incentive
Free minutes and FnF Min will not available during IR
Packages are recursive in charging (monthly) and pro-ratable
No CPP charges will be applied on these packages
GPRS rates would be the Rs.18/MB with 64KB minimum charging unit
Package is available to consumer catalogue only & not business
If an FnF number is changed or added, it will take effect from the next day. If a number is deleted or replaced, it will end on the same day at 23:59, as per current scenario for all existing packages
An FnF number added or updated cannot be deleted again on the same day. Delete action can only work from the next day
If an FnF number ports out, the FnF discount will no longer apply to calls made to it

 

Offer Mechanics:

  • Applicable on all existing Consumer Postpaid subscribers [Jazz & Warid], New SIM Sales, Pre to Post Conversions, and Port-Ins
  • All other mechanics of the Price-Plan remain the same

• Base rate is 0.10/MB

  • Other VAS and Invoice details will be charged (where applicable).

  • Ex PMCL package user gets all bolt on packages as normal postpaid customer can get
  • Now minimum deposit of Rs 1,000 will be required for official to Ex PMCL package conversion and credit limit will be set as per deposit amount .

Incentives include 150 SMS on all networks

An FnF number added or updated cannot be deleted again on the same day. Delete action can only work from the next day
If an FnF number ports out, the FnF discount will no longer apply to calls made to it

column36:
Date: 2-July-2025

Gold Basic has been removed from Postpaid New Sale/Pre-Post Conversions as price and resources have been matched with Gold Value.

Effective 2-July-2025, we will not offer Gold Basic(699) for Postpaid New Sale as well as for Pre to Post Conversion, instead, we can offer Gold Value or other available plans;

1- Gold Value

2- Gold Plus

3- Jazz Red

4- Jazz Red Z

 

Offer Mechanics:

  • All Price Plans are monthly recursive and pro-ratable;
  • Maximum of 3 F&F numbers will be allowed;
  • 4x Data Offer (For New Acquisition) will not be available for the New Price Plans.

Important Points

 

Gold Basic to Gold Classic Migration:

  1. 30k Customers on Gold Basic (PKR 750incl tax) will be migrated to Gold Classic (PKR 850 with additional 500 On Net Mins and 500 SMS) on 2nd Jun 2023.  
  2. These customers have been sent a broadcast on 23rd May, the content of which is shared below: 

“Dear Customer, From 2-Jun-23, you will get 10GB, 3500 Onnet Min, 200 Offnet Min & 3500 SMS in only Rs.850 (Inc.Tax)/Month. Stay connected with Jazz Super 4G.” 

  1. The customers calling on helpline before 1st Jun 2023 to revert their package will be excluded from Package Migration Activity.  
  2. The customers calling between 1st Jun to 25th Jun 2023 will be reverted on Gold Basic on 2nd July 2023 and a credit note of PKR 100 will be posted to ensure positive customer experience 
  3. The customers calling between 26th Jun to 25th July 2023 will be reverted on Gold Basic on 2nd Aug 2023 and a credit note of PKR 200 will be posted to ensure positive customer experience. 
  4. Any customer requesting a package reversal after 25th July 2023 will not be entertained.

column36:
Date: 2-July-2025

Gold Basic has been removed from Postpaid New Sale/Pre-Post Conversions as price and resources have been matched with Gold Value.

Effective 2-July-2025, we will not offer Gold Basic(699) for Postpaid New Sale as well as for Pre to Post Conversion, instead, we can offer Gold Value or other available plans;

1- Gold Value

2- Gold Plus

3- Jazz Red

4- Jazz Red Z

 

Offer Mechanics:

  • All Price Plans are monthly recursive and pro-ratable;
  • Maximum of 3 F&F numbers will be allowed;
  • 4x Data Offer (For New Acquisition) will not be available for the New Price Plans.

Important Points

 

Gold Basic to Gold Classic Migration:

  1. 30k Customers on Gold Basic (PKR 750incl tax) will be migrated to Gold Classic (PKR 850 with additional 500 On Net Mins and 500 SMS) on 2nd Jun 2023.  
  2. These customers have been sent a broadcast on 23rd May, the content of which is shared below: 

“Dear Customer, From 2-Jun-23, you will get 10GB, 3500 Onnet Min, 200 Offnet Min & 3500 SMS in only Rs.850 (Inc.Tax)/Month. Stay connected with Jazz Super 4G.” 

  1. The customers calling on helpline before 1st Jun 2023 to revert their package will be excluded from Package Migration Activity.  
  2. The customers calling between 1st Jun to 25th Jun 2023 will be reverted on Gold Basic on 2nd July 2023 and a credit note of PKR 100 will be posted to ensure positive customer experience 
  3. The customers calling between 26th Jun to 25th July 2023 will be reverted on Gold Basic on 2nd Aug 2023 and a credit note of PKR 200 will be posted to ensure positive customer experience. 
  4. Any customer requesting a package reversal after 25th July 2023 will not be entertained.

column95:
Dear All

We are pleased to announce the inclusion of the Usage History option in the self-service menus (*444# for prepaid and *446# for postpaid customers).

This enhancement allows customers to conveniently check their last 10 transactions, including Calls, SMS, and Data, with proper validations (CNIC/NTN/Passport Number). Customers can access this feature by dialing *444# or *446# and following the instructions provided

Select Duration:

  1. Last 24 Hours
  2. Last 7 Days

Select Usage Categories:

  • Calls
  • SMS
  • Data

This initiative aims to enhance customer satisfaction by providing greater transparency and ease of access to usage details, supporting our commitment to delivering superior services.
